5:
Do you think this is enough for
dinner? We shouldn't need too
much since we'll make it to Palpebra
tomorrow.
10:
Indeed. Let's set up camp before the
sun setsâ€”
19: I... I can do this! Ahhh!
29:
W-wow, that was amazing! You
swooped in just like Grindle would've!
41:
I-I'm all right! Thank you so much for
rescuing me! I'm Millet, by the way.
46:
The monsters in this area aren't the
most dangerous, but they are still
formidable.
48:
A young child like you should take
care not to wander here alone.
53:
Oh... I'll be more careful in the
future... But, um... I'm actually an
adventurer...
57:
Y-you are? My apologies, I didn't
mean to cause offense...
62:
It's okay! I know I've still got a long
ways to go.
65:
That's why I came to this forest. I
wanted to train and get stronger,
but then I got lost...
71:
Sounds to me like it's chow time.
Want to join us for dinner?
75:
This is delicious! I can't believe
you're good at fighting AND cooking,
Alk!
79:
Oh, I'm only okay at it. Honestly,
you're the good one. You moved like
a pro while we were cooking.
83:
I've just got experience under my
belt. My family runs an inn, so I've
been helping out since I was young.
86:
I actually like doing household
chores... Ehehe.
91:
Is that so? Why did you decide to
become an adventurer, then?
94:
Er, that's because... I was inspired by
the Grindle Tales.
99:
Ah, that's the book series about a
party of adventurers, isn't it? Pretty
popular too, from what Stella told
meâ€”
104:
Yes, that's exactly the one! The main
character is super cool, but I love
the main heroine the most!
106:
Her name's Patty, and she's good at
fighting and support! I want to be an
adventurer exactly like her!
110:
Ah! I'm s-sorry, it's kind of lame to be
inspired by stories, isn't it...
114:
I don't think so. Lots of adventurers
were inspired by something, and it's
not my place to judge.
119:
Exactly. Everyone has one reason or
another driving them, and yours is
as valid as the rest.
124:
You really think so? Ehehe... Thanks
for saying as much.
128:
I'm still new at all this, but... One day,
I'll definitely become an awesome
fighter and supporter like Patty!
133: She matters to you that much, huh?
137:
I'm feeling a little inspired myself. I've
gotta keep working hard too!
143:
Oh, Alk! Light! Thanks again for the
other day!
147:
Hey, Millet. Getting a job from Lilie
today?
152:
She is, but... Would you mind
partying up with her from today
forward?
156:
Of course we don't mind, but what
brought this on?
159:
It's part of a new system the Guild's
trying out.
162:
A lot of new adventurers don't make
it back from the field, so we're trying
to pair them up with more
experienced people to show them
the ropes.
165:
Since this is an official request, you'll
also be paid for your time. How
about it?
170:
We have no issues taking this on. In
fact, this is a wonderful ideaâ€”one I
can tell you fought to implement.
175:
Are you sure we're the best ones for
the job though? There are plenty of
experienced adventurers who could
teach Millet more...
180:
I asked specifically f-for you! Since
we already knew each other, I
figured it would be better...
184:
I-I'll definitely listen to what you
have to say! Please, teach me your
ways! Throw me in the brig if I mess
up!
188:
Wh-whoa, there! We're adventurers,
not a band of pirates!
192:
If you're truly fine with us as
mentors, then we'd be happy to
help. Looking forward to working
with you, Millet.
199:
I'll do my best to back you up, no
matter how hard I have to work!
Ehehe...
202: I can't wait to head out!
